	      <B><FONT COLOR="#000000">About Haskell-Cafe</FONT></B>
	    </TD>
            <TD COLSPAN="1" WIDTH="100%" BGCOLOR="#FFF0D0">
              <FORM Method=POST ACTION="../listinfo/haskell-cafe"> English (USA)
              </FORM>
            </TD>
	  </TR>
	    <tr>
	      <td colspan="2">
		<P><!---->This mailing list is for the discussion of topics related to Haskell. The volume may at times be high, as the scope is broader than the main Haskell mailing list.  Discussions on the Haskell mailing list which have drifted off topic, or are only of interest to a small number of subscribers, will be asked to move to Haskell-Cafe.<br><br>Please don't crosspost to both haskell and haskell-cafe.<!----></P>
	  <p> To see the collection of prior postings to the list,
	      visit the <a href="http://www.haskell.org/pipermail/haskell-cafe/">Haskell-Cafe
		  Archives</a>.
	      
	  </p>
	</TD>
      </TR>
      <TR>
	<TD COLSPAN="2" WIDTH="100%" BGCOLOR="#FFF0D0">
	  <B><FONT COLOR="#000000">Using Haskell-Cafe</FONT></B>
	</TD>
      </TR>
      <tr>
	<td colspan="2">
	  To post a message to all the list members, send email to
	  <A HREF="mailto:haskell-cafe@haskell.org">haskell-cafe@haskell.org</A>.

	  <p>You can subscribe to the list, or change your existing
	    subscription, in the sections below.
	</td>
      </tr>
      <TR>
	<TD COLSPAN="2" WIDTH="100%" BGCOLOR="#FFF0D0">
	  <B><FONT COLOR="#000000">Subscribing to Haskell-Cafe</FONT></B>
	</TD>
      </TR>
      <tr>
	<td colspan="2">
	  <P>
	    Subscribe to Haskell-Cafe by filling out the following
	      form.
	  You will be sent email requesting confirmation, to
            prevent others from gratuitously subscribing you. This is a hidden list, which means that the
            list of members is available only to the list administrator.
	  <ul>
    <FORM Method=POST ACTION="../subscribe/haskell-cafe">
	      <TABLE BORDER="0" CELLSPACING="2" CELLPADDING="2"
		WIDTH="70%">
		<TR>
